# Wallet Auth (SIWE)

Wallet connection and Sign-In With Ethereum are wired in `src/components/app-providers.tsx`. `WagmiProvider` (config from `src/lib/wagmi.ts`) wraps `RainbowKitAuthenticationProvider` + `RainbowKitProvider`. The wagmi config (`getDefaultConfig`, chains `mainnet`/`sepolia`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID`) is shared by both wagmi and RainbowKit.

## Sign-in flow
`AppProviders` builds a RainbowKit `createAuthenticationAdapter`. After a wallet connects via `<ConnectButton />` (`src/components/header.tsx`), RainbowKit drives:
1. `getNonce` → `authClient.siwe.nonce({ walletAddress, chainId })`.
2. `createMessage` → `createSiweMessage` from `viem/siwe`.
3. `verify` → `authClient.siwe.verify({ message, signature, walletAddress, chainId })`; on success it `router.push('/protected')`.
`authStatus` is derived from `authClient.useSession()` (loading/authenticated/unauthenticated).

## Better Auth SIWE config
The `siwe()` plugin is registered in `src/lib/auth/auth.ts`: `getNonce`, and `verifyMessage` using viem's `verifyMessage`. The client mirror lives in `src/lib/auth/auth-client.ts` via `siweClient()`. The HTTP handler is `src/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`.

## Route protection
- `src/proxy.ts` — checks `auth.api.getSession`; `PUBLIC_ROUTES` (only `/`) is reachable logged out, everything else redirects to `/`.
- `src/app/protected/layout.tsx` — server layout re-checks the session and redirects to `/` if absent.

## Add a protected page
Create the route under `src/app/protected/`; the layout guards it. Add a path to `PUBLIC_ROUTES` in `src/proxy.ts` only if it must stay public.
